# MovieList — project baseline

## Prescribed stack

- **React Native CLI** (not Expo). TypeScript **`strict`**.
- **React Navigation v6** only — bottom tabs + nested stack per tab.
- **Zustand** for global state only; **AsyncStorage** for persisted watchlist.
- **Axios** only via **`src/api/client.ts`**. Never `import axios` outside `src/api/`.
- **`StyleSheet.create` only** for styles.
- **Manrope + Inter** via theme / `react-native-google-fonts` — no ad-hoc font families in screens.
- Remote TMDB data only through **`src/hooks/`**. **`src/screens/**`** must not call TMDB or wire HTTP directly.

## Prohibited

- NativeWind, Styled Components, CSS-in-JS.
- Redux, MobX, or any global state library other than Zustand.
- UI kits (Paper, Elements, etc.).
- Nav libraries other than React Navigation v6.
- **Hardcoded API keys or tokens** in source, tests, or docs.

## Environment

- **`react-native-dotenv`**. **`.env`** is gitignored; **`.env.example`** holds placeholders only.
- Bearer token for TMDB only from env, consumed in **`src/api/client.ts`** (typed `@env` declarations).

## Hooks contract

- Data hooks expose **`{ data, loading, error, refetch }`** (align with `UseQueryResult`).

## Parallel async

- Independent parallel sections (e.g. detail) use **`Promise.allSettled`**, with per-section handling of success/failure.

## Null-safety (UI + data)

- Defensively handle **poster, backdrop, runtime, rating**, and **empty arrays** — no assumed non-null media metadata.

## Theme

- Colours and spacing **only** from **`src/theme/colors.ts`** and **`src/theme/spacing.ts`**.
- **No 1px layout borders** (“no-line” rule).
- **No pure `#FFFFFF`** for text — use theme text colours.

## TypeScript

- No **`any`**. API/TMDB shapes in **`src/api/types.ts`**. Navigation params in **`src/navigation/types.ts`**.

## Folder layout

- Standard **`src/`** tree: **`api/`**, **`components/`**, **`hooks/`**, **`navigation/`**, **`screens/`**, **`store/`**, **`theme/`**, **`utils/`**. Do not invent a parallel or duplicate structure.
